			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://allthingsliberty.com/2020/09/the-first-efforts-to-limit-the-african-slave-trade-arise-in-the-american-revolution-part-2-of-3-the-middle-and-southern-colonies/" rel="bookmark">The First Efforts to Limit the African Slave Trade Arise in the American Revolution: Part 2 of 3, The Middle and Southern Colonies</a></h2>			<div class="entry-summary">
				<p>The first article of this series discussed the increasing chorus of American Patriots in New England raising their voices against the African slave trade. This article focuses on the Middle and Southern Colonies, as well as a few select thinkers from Philadelphia. Those who opposed the African slave trade in colonies ruled by royal governors [&hellip;]</p>
			</div><!-- .entry-summary -->
			
			<span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://allthingsliberty.com/author/christian-mcburney/">by	Christian McBurney</a></span>
		</div>
	</div>
</article><!-- #post-18704 -->

